name: Treat Her Like A Lady

lyrics:

Now I'm the kinda guy,
Who don't be-lieve that chivalry is dead, no.
'Cos I believe a woman,
Should be treated with the utmost re-spect, mmm-hmm...
 Don't be afraid; don't turn and walk a-way,
I wanna get to know ya, well.
 Don't be ashamed; don't say that love's to blame,
Just come and look me over.
(You'll find a heart), you'll find a heart,
That you've always been lookin' for.

 Treat her like a lady, (treat her like lady).
Light her cigarette if she smokes, even, (help her with her coat);

In this world of liberation, it's so easy to for-get, mmm...

You can bet, bet you can, baby.

 Ever since that day, her words never went a-way,
I always will remember, to treat my baby tender.

 Treat her like a lady, (treat her like lady).

Another summer Another vacation is over... 
A September morning, With the sun and the smell of the clover...
Down by the gates We sit and we watch all our friends go by... 
And pretend we don't hear the bell, That rings through the summer sky.
I was happy with the kisses she gave me, 
It's just that happy was all she made me... 
Happy that was... Until I saw you...
Heartbeat, heartbeat, Why do you fail me now? 
You hurt me...desert me, In my darkest hour... 
Heartbeat, heartbeat, Why do you keep me here? 
How could I help but admire her beauty? 
Standing on the line between desire and duty... 
Heartbeat Heartbeat... It will end in tears...
I need a lover, But loves such a dangerous place to be... 
Oh, if we were meant for each other, Then why don't you answer me?
Don't keep me waiting, You know that I long to be by your side... 
We could even be together, Tonight...
I was happy with the kisses she gave me... 
Now there's nothing on Earth that can save me... 
Why should I care? I can't have you....
Heartbeat, heartbeat, Why do you fail me now? 
You hurt me...desert me, In my darkest hour... 
Heartbeat, heartbeat, Why do you keep me here? 
How could I help but admire her beauty? 
Standing on the line between desire and duty... 
Heartbeat Heartbeat... It will end in tears...
